<h2 id="installation">Installation</h2>
<blockquote>
  <p>Procedure on <a href="https://terminalroot.com.br/linux">Linux</a></p>
</blockquote>

<ul>
  <li><strong>1</strong>. - Install the dependencies
First you will need to have it installed on your system:</li>
  <li><a href="https://openjdk.java.net/">JDK</a> - Java development environment;</li>
  <li>and <a href="https://icedtea.classpath.org">IcedTea</a> - An integration software.</li>
</ul>

<p>Use your distribution‚Äôs package manager to install them, for example, as I installed here on <a href="https://terminalroot.com.br/2017/05/how-install-o-gentoo.html">Gentoo</a>:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">sudo </span><span class="nv">USE</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"-cups -alsa"</span> emerge <span class="nt">-a</span> dev-java/openjdk-bin dev-java/openjdk-jre-bin</code></pre></figure>

<blockquote>
  <p>In this case I rejected the modules: <em>cups</em> and <em>alsa</em> and icedtea was installed automatically as it is a dependency.</p>
</blockquote>

<ul>
  <li><strong>2</strong>. - Installing <a href="https://www.jython.org/">Jython</a></li>
</ul>

<p>Now download Jython at: <a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/jython/">https://sourceforge.net/projects/jython/</a>. After downloading extract the package:</p>
<blockquote>
  <p>Create and enter a directory first so that files are not scattered</p>
</blockquote>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">mkdir </span>environment <span class="o">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class="nb">cd </span>environment/
<span class="nb">mv</span> ../jython<span class="k">*</span> <span class="nb">.</span>
jar xj jython.jar
java <span class="nt">-jar</span> jython_installer-<span class="k">*</span>.jar</code></pre></figure>

<p>After this last command, it will open a ** wizard ** for you to follow, follow the images below:</p>

