<p>After <strong>finish</strong> we will now edit your <code class="highlighter-rouge">vim ~/.bashrc</code> and add the following line:</p>
<blockquote>
  <p>In this case my version and directory name is <strong>2.5.2</strong>, check yours.</p>
</blockquote>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nv">PATH</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">PATH</span><span class="k">}</span><span class="s2">:</span><span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">HOME</span><span class="k">}</span><span class="s2">/jython2.5.2/bin/"</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>Then run the <code class="highlighter-rouge">source ~/.bashrc</code> command or close and open the terminal so that the <code class="highlighter-rouge">jython</code> command can be found.</p>

